  "body": "Contract: Foo.sol\r\nCompiler: 0.8.17+commit.8df45f5f\r\n\r\n```\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-3.0\r\npragma solidity >=0.8.12 <0.9.0;\r\ncontract Foo {\r\n    function foo() private pure returns (uint) {\r\n        return 1 + 2;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n![GasEstimate](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10043091/196052051-05fa9b1a-1305-472a-b1bc-e992013823dd.png)\r\n\r\nRemix estimates \"infinite gas\" for this function despite it only adding two known numbers together.\r\nI would expect the estimation to be a bit more accurate than that...",
