    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "That happens because the function is private, only have to change it to public/external, or call it in a public/external one and the gas estimation will be the expected one.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"494\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-06-30 at 20 57 27\" src=\"https://github.com/ethereum/remix-project/assets/26546018/db5c5aee-9210-4204-8916-01f1f3ca3204\">\r\n\r\nIt looks like the private/internal functions gas calculation in `solc` is set to infinite and not changed unless it has an entry point.\r\n",
